The Chronicle Showbiz Reporter Veteran ZBC Radio disc jockey, Peter John’s has died. The former Radio 3 DJ died at a hospital in London on Monday after battling three strokes and a heart operation. Peter Johns, who was affectionately known as “PJ Your DJ” or “The Radio Driver”, hosted the Midday Jam on Radio 3 (now Power FM) in Zimbabwe. He left the station in 2002.